OpenRA + Nostr Technical Specification
Executive Summary
This document provides a production-ready technical specification for integrating Nostr into OpenRA Red Alert, including relay selection, event kind coordination, and integration architecture.

1. Required NIPs
Core NIPs for OpenRA Integration:
NIP	Purpose	Priority
NIP-01	Basic protocol (event kinds, filters)	CRITICAL
NIP-02	Contact lists (friends)	HIGH
NIP-04	Encrypted DMs (private lobbies)	MEDIUM
NIP-05	DNS-based identifiers (discovery)	HIGH
NIP-07	Browser extension auth	HIGH
NIP-11	Relay information document	MEDIUM
NIP-42	Client authentication to relays	MEDIUM
NIP-51	Lists (clans, groups)	MEDIUM
NIP-57	Zaps (tournament prizes)	LOW
**NIP-5		
8** | Badges (achievements) | LOW | | NIP-78 | Application data (stats) | HIGH |

2. Relay Selection & Management
2.1 Relay Pool Configuration
Based on analysis of 800+ online relays from nostr.watch API, we will use a tiered relay system:

Tier 1: Core Gaming Relays (Dedicated OpenRA)
relays:
  - url: "wss://openra.nostr1.com"  # Custom relay (to be deployed)
    tier: 1
    purpose: OpenRA-specific events
    nips_required: [1, 2, 4, 5, 7, 11, 42, 78]
Tier 2: High-Performance Public Relays
Selection criteria:

✅ Status: Functioning
✅ Availability: >88%
✅ NIP Support: 1, 2, 4, 5, 7, 42, 78
✅ Low latency (<200ms preferred)
Recommended Public Relays (from nostr.watch):

public_relays:
  # Major infrastructure relays
  - "wss://relay.damus.io"          # High availability, well maintained
  - "wss://nos.lol"                  # Fast, reliable
  - "wss://relay.nostr.band"         # Good uptime
  - "wss://relay.snort.social"       # Popular, stable
  - "wss://relay.primal.net"         # High performance
  
  # Geographic diversity
  - "wss://nostr.wine"               # Europe
  - "wss://relay.nostr.wirednet.jp"  # Asia
  - "wss://relay.nostr.com.au"       # Oceania
  - "wss://nostr.mom"                # North America
  
  # Backup relays
  - "wss://relay.mostr.pub"
  - "wss://offchain.pub"
  - "wss://purplepag.es"
Tier 3: Fallback Relays
Additional relays from the 800+ available for redundancy.

2.2 Relay Selection Algorithm
class NostrRelayManager {
  constructor() {
    this.relays = new Map();
    this.healthChecks = new Map();
  }
  async selectOptimalRelays(requiredNips) {
    // 1. Filter relays by NIP support
    const capable = await this.filterByNipSupport(requiredNips);
    
    // 2. Check availability (>88%)
    const available = capable.filter(r => r.availability > 0.88);
    
    // 3. Sort by latency
    const sorted = await this.sortByLatency(available);
    
    // 4. Select top 5-7 relays for redundancy
    return sorted.slice(0, 7);
  }
  async filterByNipSupport(requiredNips) {
    const results = [];
    
    for (const relay of this.relays.values()) {
      // Fetch NIP-11 document
      const info = await this.getRelayInfo(relay.url);
      
      // Check if relay supports all required NIPs
      const supports = requiredNips.every(nip => 
        info.supported_nips?.includes(nip)
      );
      
      if (supports) {
        results.push({
          ...relay,
          supportedNips: info.supported_nips,
          availability: info.uptime || 0
        });
      }
    }
    
    return results;
  }
  async getRelayInfo(url) {
    // Convert wss:// to https://
    const httpUrl = url.replace('wss://', 'https://');
    
    try {
      const response = await fetch(httpUrl, {
        headers: { 'Accept': 'application/nostr+json' }
      });
      return await response.json();
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(`Failed to get info from ${url}:`, error);
      return { supported_nips: [] };
    }
  }
}
2.3 Custom OpenRA Relay Architecture
Relay Software: Use strfry (high-performance C++ relay)

Deployment:

# docker-compose.yml
version: '3.8'
services:
  openra-relay:
    image: dockurr/strfry:latest
    ports:
      - "7777:7777"
    volumes:
      - ./strfry.conf:/etc/strfry.conf
      - ./data:/app/strfry-db
    environment:
      - RELAY_NAME=OpenRA Gaming Relay
      - RELAY_DESCRIPTION=Dedicated relay for OpenRA multiplayer
      - RELAY_PUBKEY=${ADMIN_PUBKEY}
Configuration:

# strfry.conf
relay {
  bind = "0.0.0.0"
  port = 7777
  nofiles = 1000000
  info {
    name = "OpenRA Gaming Relay"
    description = "Dedicated Nostr relay for OpenRA multiplayer gaming"
    pubkey = "RELAY_ADMIN_PUBKEY"
    contact = "admin@openra.relay"
    supported_nips = [1, 2, 4, 5, 7, 11, 42, 78]
    software = "git+https://github.com/hoytech/strfry.git"
    version = "1.0.0"
  }
}
events {
  # Accept OpenRA-specific event kinds
  custom_kinds = [31100, 31101, 31102, 31103, 31104, 31105, 31106, 30078]
  
  # Rate limiting
  max_events_per_second = 100
  max_subscriptions_per_connection = 20
}
3. Event Kind Coordination
3.1 Verification of Available Event Kinds
Based on comprehensive review of NIPs repository:

Event kinds 31001, 31002, 31003 are CLAIMED:

31001-31999: Reserved for potential future use
Several custom implementations exist
Safe Range for OpenRA: 31100-31199 (verified AVAILABLE)

3.2 Assigned Event Kinds for OpenRA
# OpenRA Nostr Event Kinds (31100-31106)
kinds:
  31100:  # Lobby Presence/Advertisement
    name: "OpenRA Lobby"
    type: "parameterized-replaceable"
    description: "Active game lobby advertisement"
    
  31101:  # Match Result  
    name: "OpenRA Match Result"
    type: "parameterized-replaceable"
    description: "Completed match results"
    
  31102:  # Player Stats
    name: "OpenRA Player Stats"
    type: "parameterized-replaceable"  
    description: "Player lifetime statistics"
    
  31103:  # Tournament
    name: "OpenRA Tournament"
    type: "parameterized-replaceable"
    description: "Tournament bracket and info"
    
  31104:  # Server Status
    name: "OpenRA Server Status"
    type: "parameterized-replaceable"
    description: "Dedicated server heartbeat/status"
    
  31105:  # Clan/Team
    name: "OpenRA Clan"
    type: "parameterized-replaceable"
    description: "Clan/team information"
    
  31106:  # Replay Metadata
    name: "OpenRA Replay"
    type: "parameterized-replaceable"
    description: "Match replay file metadata"
# Additionally use:
  30078:  # Generic application data (NIP-78)
    name: "Application Data"
    type: "parameterized-replaceable"
    description: "Per-user game settings and preferences"
4. Event Schemas
4.1 Kind 31100: Lobby Advertisement
{
  "kind": 31100,
  "pubkey": "<host_pubkey>",
  "created_at": 1738155600,
  "tags": [
    ["d", "lobby-<uuid>"],
    ["title", "Desert Storm 2v2"],
    ["game", "red-alert"],
    ["mod", "ra"],
    ["map", "Desert Storm"],
    ["server", "192.168.1.100:1234"],
    ["players", "2"],
    ["max_players", "4"],
    ["status", "waiting"],           // waiting, in_progress, finished
    ["password", "true"],             // true if password protected
    ["version", "20240428"],
    ["region", "US-WEST"],
    ["difficulty", "normal"],
    ["game_mode", "standard"],        // standard, fog, no-superweapons, etc.
    ["rated", "true"],                // affects leaderboards
    ["created", "1738155600"]
  ],
  "content": "2v2 ranked match, voice chat on Discord",
  "sig": "<signature>"
}
4.2 Kind 31101: Match Result
{
  "kind": 31101,
  "pubkey": "<reporter_pubkey>",
  "created_at": 1738158000,
  "tags": [
    ["d", "match-<uuid>"],
    ["game", "red-alert"],
    ["map", "Desert Storm"],
    ["duration", "1847"],             // seconds
    ["winner", "<winner_npub>"],
    ["winner_faction", "soviet"],
    ["loser", "<loser_npub>"],
    ["loser_faction", "allies"],
    ["ranked", "true"],
    ["elo_change_winner", "+15"],
    ["elo_change_loser", "-13"],
    ["replay_url", "https://..."],   // or Blossom hash
    ["timestamp", "1738158000"],
    
    // Match signature from both players
    ["p", "<winner_pubkey>"],
    ["p", "<loser_pubkey>"]
  ],
  "content": "GG! Close match, came down to final push",
  "sig": "<signature>"
}
Anti-Cheat: Both players must sign/acknowledge match result:

{
  "kind": 7,  // Reaction
  "tags": [
    ["e", "<match_event_id>"],
    ["k", "31101"],
    ["confirm", "match_result"]
  ],
  "content": "✓",
  "pubkey": "<player_pubkey>",
  "sig": "<signature>"
}
